mindmap
  root((Type-2 Diabetes Reversal Research))
    Definitions
      Remission: normal HbA1c off diabetes meds for 3+ months
      Reversal used interchangeably; not a permanent cure
      ADA and Diabetes UK consensus frameworks
    Mechanisms
      Twin Cycle: liver fat drives pancreatic fat buildup
      Pancreatic fat impairs beta-cell insulin secretion
      Weight loss restores beta-cell function
      Beta-cell dedifferentiation may partially reverse
      Visceral fat drives insulin resistance
    Interventions
      Low-calorie diets: DiRECT 46% remission at 1 year
      Sustained loss of 10-15 kg often needed
      Low-carb and Mediterranean patterns
      Bariatric surgery: 50-80% remission in trials
      Lifestyle: diet plus activity plus support
      GLP-1 drugs: strong control; remission data emerging
    Key trials
      DiRECT: primary-care weight management
      Look AHEAD: weight benefits; limited formal remission
      2025 meta-analyses confirm multicomponent approaches
      Surgery RCTs: 8x remission vs medical care at 1 year
    Success predictors
      Shorter diabetes duration
      Higher baseline beta-cell reserve
      Greater sustained weight loss
      Lower starting HbA1c and fewer meds
      Lean T2D and long-standing disease harder
    Limitations
      Relapse common if weight regained
      Durability beyond 5 years still studied
      Access cost and behavioral sustainability
      Individual variation; no single protocol
